<metal:block i18n:domain="schooltool.gradebook">
  <div class="header" i18n:translate="">
    What is This?
  </div>
  <div class="body">
    <p i18n:translate="">
      This form allows you to change the weighting of categories when
      calculating average scores within a worksheet.
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      Enter numeric values for each relevant category.
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      For example, to weight exams as 60% of the grade, homework as
      20% and quizzes as 20%, enter "60" next to "Exam", "20" next to
      "Homework" and "20" next to "Quiz".
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="">
      The list of categories can be customized for your school by your
      system administrator.
    </p>
  </div>
</metal:block>
